00:00:23.298 --> 00:00:26.396
I'll be making Mixed Vegetable Stew

00:00:32.819 --> 00:00:35.690
Ingredients required to make Mixed Vegetable Stew

00:00:36.041 --> 00:00:51.120
Tamarind, Brinjal (Egg Plant), Lima Beans, Fenugreek, Green Chilli, Carrot, Coriander,
 Sesame, Niger Seeds, Seasoning Seeds, Oil, Salt, Turmeric, Jaggery, Onions, 

00:00:51.654 --> 00:00:55.364
First, soak the tamarind in water

00:01:01.709 --> 00:01:05.830
Take a pot and heat some water

00:01:07.332 --> 00:01:16.414
Add a few egg plants into the water

00:01:18.604 --> 00:01:25.274
A few lima beans

00:01:26.894 --> 00:01:35.254
Some green chilli &amp; carrot

00:01:37.828 --> 00:01:43.929
Boil for 5 minutes

00:02:22.768 --> 00:02:28.199
Keep the cooked green chillies aside

00:02:30.275 --> 00:02:35.851
Take a cup of fried niger seeds and add them to the green chillies

00:02:37.547 --> 00:02:44.915
Now, add fried sesame seeds to it and grind them into a paste

00:02:47.026 --> 00:03:08.398
Squeeze out the egg plants til only the skin is left into the tamarind juice
and discard the skin

00:03:10.288 --> 00:03:25.275
Add the rest of the cooked vegetables into the tamarind juice

00:03:32.214 --> 00:03:37.231
Add some salt

00:03:51.896 --> 00:03:57.261
Now, add the ground sesame, chilli and niger seeds paste to the tamarind juice

00:04:24.355 --> 00:04:29.327
Take a pot and heat some oil

00:04:29.936 --> 00:04:50.380
Add some mustard seeds, cumin, dry red chilli, curry leaves, turmeric, fenugreek and fry them

00:04:52.865 --> 00:04:59.469
Meanwhile, add some jaggery to the stew

00:05:02.847 --> 00:05:12.620
Add the fried seasoning seeds and leaves to the stew

00:05:15.434 --> 00:05:23.868
Garnish with some coriander leaves &amp; onions

